article.headline: Maryland 78, Colorado 71
article.story: SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico -- Terrell Stoglin scored 32 points to lead Maryland to a 78-71 victory over Colorado on Friday in the Puerto Rico Tip-Off. Stoglin tied the single-game tournament record with 12 field goals, including 4-for-7 on 3-pointers, and keyed the run that put the Terrapins (2-1) ahead to stay. Sean Mosley added 16 points and Nick Faust 15. Andre Roberson had a double-double for the Buffaloes (1-2) with 21 points and 13 rebounds. Carlon Brown scored 14 points and Austin Dufault 12 for Colorado, which led by 12 in the first half. Roberson gave Colorado a 60-56 lead with 8:25 left. But Stoglin scored eight straight to finish an 11-0 run that put Maryland ahead 67-60 with 6:01 left. The Terrapins hit 49 percent (27 of 55) and shot 52 percent (11 of 21) from 3-point range. Maryland will play Iona for fifth place Sunday. Colorado will face Western Michigan for seventh.
